HEADWORD: Medullated
<hw>Me*dul"la*ted</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <fld>(Anat.)</fld>
<def>Furnished with a medulla or marrow, or with a medullary sheath;
<as>as, a <ex>medullated</ex> nerve fiber</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

